Comments.Message:
I think this is a simple case of misunderstanding and mis-communication.
@cjbard- I opened the file you attached and looked at the trinket list. You are correct in that that list includes several JC/Alch/Eng trinkets such as figurines (serpent,owl,hare), Alchem. stones (Mighty & Mercurial), Enginneering (Noise Machine/Lightning Gen) (BTW these are the specifics Astry was asking for). I then looked at your filters from the attached file but contrary to your claim, the "Crafted" checkbox IS selected and therefore allowing crafted items (both BoP and BoE) to be listed. Unchecking the box causes ALL of these items to disappear from the list (as expected).
If by chance you were trying to filter out the crafted BoP trinkets, you can go further down the filter list and check the "Disable BoP Crafted" which removes all items except the Noise Machine (since it is BoE).
As for Shadowmourne, it is not listed under Main Hand for your posted character and i failed to get Shadowmourne to ever show up regardless of which filters were selected or deselected (which is actually a success since your a shaman).
Everything you mentioned in the OP is working as intented with your attached toon and therefore unrepeatable to others. If you are still having problems, I suggest you restart your toon from scratch using Character Profiler and/or Armoury. If still having the issue, try a fresh download. 

@Binkenstein-Hinalover's comment applies to you. The items are listed in the posted toon for the shoulder slots but immediately are removed by deselecting the "Armor Tokens" box.

@Boo - Maybe the easiest and quickest way for you to filter the other items by their iLevel vice the toon level using them. Go back to your filter and select "Disable by Item Level" and start at the highest level and select them downward (probably leaving only heirloom and tier 1-6 unmarked). This will remove all the items iLevel 200 and up, leaving you with only quest and non-heroic items usually obtainable pre-level 80.

I use something similar to this on my recently leveled Boomkin to guide me to quest rewards that I haven't done in Northrend and to particular instances that drop upgrades. Let me know if this helped you out.

(BTW please remember that some things will be off a little or possibly a lot since Rawr is designed for lvl 80 characters.)
